    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-05-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="261"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/5–2448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of Naval Operations</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Denfeld</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Commander of the United States Naval
                        Forces, Western Pacific</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Badger</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="14" xml:id="d261fn14">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Navy Department on May 13.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-05-12">12 May
                            1948</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122227Z. Your 030045 and 100835.<note n="15" xml:id="d261fn15">Latter not
                        printed.</note> Whole problem of presence our forces in Tsingtao being
                    forwarded to SecDefense<note n="16" xml:id="d261fn16">James Forrestal.</note>
                    recommending reference to SecState. Pending further instructions JCS<note n="17"
                        xml:id="d261fn17">Joint Chiefs of Staff.</note> approve your general course
                    of action <hi rend="italic">a</hi> if situation requires.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
